transcript.text: Hello, welcome to the On Print Shop Add on Modules tutorial series.
In this video we will learn about our Real Preview module.
The Real Preview helps your customers to know exactly how the print will look after it's printed.
The preview is available in 2D as well as in 3D based on the products and configuration.
Let's check out how the 2D and 3D preview works in the storefront.
On the storefront, when you select a product such as a business card and are on the browse design page, you can see the front and back sides of the product with the designs on a single screen.
This is the 2D preview which is generated using the mask image.
For checking the 3D preview.
Let's select a mug product on the browse design.
When you click on the preview, you can rotate the mug in all the angles and check inside out the model for folded products such as flyer, brochures, wedding invitation, etc.
You can even Click to open or close the foldings.
Please note that for 3D previews, we have two types.
One is 360° previews for flat products and the second one is for model products such as T-shirts, mug, bottle, etc.
Now let us see how you can configure these previews in your admin panel.
In the admin panel, go to the Designer Studio and click on the Studio settings.
From this screen, move to the Real Preview tab.
All the previews created will be displayed here.
To start, we need to 1st create models.
Let's create one by clicking on the real preview models.
On the next screen, you can click on the Add button.
It will take you to the next screen where you can enter the details for your new model.
Here you first need to select the preview type AS2D or 3D.
For a 2D preview, enter the title, upload the mask image, add a CSS class for this if you want to and then enter the CSS script.
After all the details, click on the save button.
For a 3D preview, you need to enter the title and select the preview model type as GLTF and script.
For the GLTF type, upload the GLTF and additional files.
Whereas for the script type, you can either enter the script for the preview or upload the Jason and additional files.
For example, in this, we have already added the GLTF file and additional files for the mug product.
After filling in all the details, click on the save button to add the new 3D model.
After creating the models, it is time to assign products to the real preview models created.
Click on the Assign Real Preview Models button from the main real preview screen.
On the next screen, select the preview type and then select Product from the first drop down.
Choose the type, specify the status of this preview display or no display and save the details.
And there you have it.
You have successfully created previews for products in 2D and 3D.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help, just reach out through live chat on on Printshop.
Com Thanks for tuning in.
